# Python
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/*.egg-info/

# OS
.DS_Store

# Local secrets — never commit (keep .env.example as the template):
**/.env.local
**/.env
!**/.env.example

# Data cache (downloaded live data)
**/data/cache/

# Backtest runs are excluded by default, BUT the reference run is kept so the
# repo renders charts + report on GitHub out-of-the-box. (Exclude the *contents*
# of outputs/, not the dir itself, so the run1 re-include can take effect.)
**/outputs/*
!**/outputs/run1/

# Keep the offline snapshots so the repo runs keyless out-of-the-box:
!**/data/offline/

# Design docs (un-ignore if you want them public):
**/PLAN.md
**/six_cycle_backtest_brief.md
